<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1323,1542]" box="[151,1195,1401,1426]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
General character states of 
<taxonomicName box="[455,506,1402,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Flax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[455,506,1402,1426]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Flax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are defined above in subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2011" box="[868,995,1401,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tentaxinae">Tentaxinae</taxonomicName>
, under diagnoses.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1323,1542]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName box="[151,202,1440,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Flax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,202,1440,1464]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Flax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 29 species, which are superficially rather variable in forewing pattern, although similar in size. As with 
<taxonomicName box="[209,290,1479,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Alienia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[209,290,1479,1503]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Alienia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it has not been possible to find convincing evidence for separating the species into separate genera, although some of the species-groups are small and have rather well-defined structures.
</paragraph>
